body: "## Context\n2026-07-04 sandbox audit: with all bundled packages installed, `pm extension --doctor` warns extension_output_service_override_global:output_format for BOTH builtin-calendar and builtin-guide-shell — two first-party packages contend for the same global output_format service, so a full first-party install is never warning-free and last-activated silently wins.\n\n## Decision needed (then implement)\nPick the owner of the global output_format override (guide-shell is the likelier owner as the interactive surface; calendar probably only needs it for its own command scope) — or scope one override to its owning commands via the action-scoped mechanism from PR#406. Record the choice as a comment here (or an ADR under pm-m2u1 if the service-ownership rule generalizes).\n\n## Definition of done\nFresh sandbox with ALL bundled packages installed shows zero doctor warnings; the ownership/scoping rule is documented in EXTENSIONS.md; regression spec asserts the doctor output stays clean."
